  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Regional Resilience Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Coffee Farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objectives:
1) Increase in income of farmers through productivity growth.
2) Facilitate access to credit and technical assistance for farmers.
3) Diversification of the crops and other economic alternatives to reduce the vulnerability of coffee producing families.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project goals :Ensure resilience of small scale farmers and members of RECOCARNO cooperatives to coffee rust. Participating farmers will directly benefit from:
1) More resilient coffee plantations through regeneration activities and the introduction of new resistant varieties;  
2) Diversified sources of income through promotion of new marketable crops, training on quality standards, and identification of new market opportunities;
3)Improved understanding of climate change and adaptation strategies through the establishment of local weather monitoring stations, training for farmers on climate change and adaptation strategies, and diversification of food crops to meet household consumption needs;
4) Access to greater social capital through strengthened cooperative governance and provision of services to members, improved capacity for advocating on behalf of small coffee farmers, and improved credit services for cooperative members.</narrative>
  </description>
